I love this park, it is only a few blocks from where I work and it offers a touch of nature. There are benches to relax on, a path that goes around the park and separated off into little paths to the the streets, and plenty of plants, flowers, and rock structures to gaze upon. The area is clean, and people mind themselves as they enjoy the area.

Discovered this hidden gem doing a Love your Park scavenger hunt. It offers sweeping views of the Philly skyline, and is a short walk from CCP and the Art Museum area. I would bring out of town visitors here for the view and history. There are terraced gardens with stone sculptures folded into the landscape. It is dog-friendly and has a shady area with benches for relaxing. The park turns 30 in 2021.

Consider yourself warned and try to enjoy the otherwise pleasant atmosphere.
